**Example component test**:
```tsx
// src/components/__tests__/PatientRiskBadge.test.tsx
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import { PatientRiskBadge } from '../PatientRiskBadge';

test('shows HIGH RISK for score > 0.8', () => {
  render(<PatientRiskBadge riskScore={0.9} patientName='Test Patient' />);
  expect(screen.getByText(/HIGH RISK/)).toBeInTheDocument();
});

test('shows LOW RISK for score < 0.5', () => {
  render(<PatientRiskBadge riskScore={0.2} patientName='Test Patient' />);
  expect(screen.getByText(/LOW RISK/)).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

**Testing hooks with TanStack Query**:
```tsx
import { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from '@tanstack/react-query';

const wrapper = ({ children }) => (
  <QueryClientProvider client={new QueryClient()}>{children}</QueryClientProvider>
);

test('usePatients returns patient list', async () => {
  const { result } = renderHook(() => usePatients(), { wrapper });
  await waitFor(() => expect(result.current.isSuccess).toBe(true));
  expect(result.current.data).toHaveLength(3);
});
```

WebSocket disconnection issues — causes and fixes:

**1. No heartbeat (most common cause of silent disconnects)**
```python
# therapeutic-copilot/server/routes/websocket_routes.py
@router.websocket('/ws/clinician/{clinician_id}')
async def clinician_ws(websocket: WebSocket, clinician_id: str):
    await websocket.accept()
    ws_manager.add_clinician(clinician_id, websocket)
    try:
        while True:
            # Add heartbeat: send ping every 30s
            try:
                data = await asyncio.wait_for(
                    websocket.receive_text(), timeout=30.0
                )
            except asyncio.TimeoutError:
                await websocket.send_text(json.dumps({'type': 'ping'}))
    except WebSocketDisconnect:
        ws_manager.remove_clinician(clinician_id, websocket)
```

**2. Frontend not handling reconnect**
```tsx
// hooks/useClinicianAlerts.ts
const reconnect = useCallback(() => {
  setTimeout(() => {
    ws.current = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:8000/ws/clinician/${clinicianId}`);
    attachHandlers(ws.current);  // Re-attach onmessage, onclose, etc.
  }, 3000);  // Reconnect after 3 seconds
}, [clinicianId]);

ws.current.onclose = () => reconnect();
```

**3. NGINX proxy timeout (production)**
```nginx
# nginx.conf — add to server block for WebSocket proxying:
location /ws/ {
    proxy_pass http://backend;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
    proxy_read_timeout 3600;  # 1 hour — default 60s will cut long sessions
}
```

**4. Redis pub/sub for multi-instance scaling (future)**
If running multiple backend instances, WebSocket rooms must use Redis pub/sub instead of in-memory dict — otherwise an alert generated on instance A won't reach a clinician connected to instance B.

The Saathi AI widget embeds on clinic websites (mindwellclinic.com, therapist-xyz.com, etc.). Those websites have their own CSS — Tailwind, Bootstrap, custom styles — that would break our widget UI if we didn't isolate it.

Shadow DOM provides complete CSS isolation:

```typescript
// widget.ts
class SaathiWidget extends HTMLElement {
  connectedCallback() {
    // Create isolated shadow tree
    const shadow = this.attachShadow({ mode: 'closed' });

    // Inject our own styles — completely isolated
    const style = document.createElement('style');
    style.textContent = `
      :host { all: initial; }  /* Reset all inherited styles */
      .chat-bubble { /* our styles, safe from host page */ }
    `;
    shadow.appendChild(style);
    shadow.appendChild(chatElement);
  }
}
customElements.define('saathi-widget', SaathiWidget);
```

**Why not iframe?** iframe is the alternative (also provides isolation). Rejected because:
1. iframe requires a separate URL to load — another server request, latency
2. Communicating between iframe and host page requires postMessage, complex
3. Shadow DOM maintains the DOM in the same page — simpler, faster
4. Vite can bundle Shadow DOM widget into a single self-contained IIFE script

**The embed code clinics use:**
```html
<script src='https://saathiai.in/widget.js' data-token='clinic-token' async></script>
```
One line. No CSS conflicts. Loads asynchronously.
